wn onion, cut into quarters"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"20 g olive oil"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"50 g sun-dried tomato pesto (see Tips)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"500 g tomato passata"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 bunches asparagus, trimmed"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","3187.5 kJ \/ 758.9 kcal","112.9 g","8.8 g","29.2 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["Ask your butcher to prepare your scallopini for you. Make sure your scallopini is thin (approx. 3 mm in thickness), otherwise cooking time may vary. Girello, a cut of beef, can replace veal in this recipe.","To make your own pesto, please refer to the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>.","For a heartier meal, add other quick-cooking vegetables to the Varoma when adding asparagus (such as green peas, snow peas or thinly sliced potatoes)."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","35m","4 portions"]}